# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Sonenta API key for the PUBLIC demo.
#
# REQUIRED FOR A PRODUCTION BUILD. Leave it unset and Vite inlines `undefined`,
# so the SDK ships `Authorization: ApiKey undefined` to every visitor and every
# authed call 401s — silently, because the CDN still serves the bundles and the
# page looks perfectly fine. That is exactly how it went unnoticed in production
# for as long as the demo has been deployed. "The demo runs" does NOT mean the
# token is set.
#
# The key is deliberately the weakest one that exists:
#   env      : prod
#   project  : 06a07109-… (demo-public) and nothing else
#   scopes   : [missing:write] and nothing else
# It can do exactly one thing: POST missing-key reports, rate-limited. REST
# reads of translations, keys and drafts return 403. It is embedded in a
# world-readable static bundle by design; worst case if leaked is junk
# missing-keys on one demo project, instantly revocable.
#
# SECURITY NOTE — DO NOT GENERALISE THIS. `missing:write` is not a
# read-restricted profile in general: backend found that
# POST /v1/auth/centrifugo-token gates on project MEMBERSHIP, not on scope, so
# such a key can still mint a realtime token and receive live translation
# updates, drafts included. Harmless HERE (this project's content is public and
# realtime is not in the prod build), but do not repeat "missing:write cannot
# read anything" as a general security claim until that backend bug is fixed.
#
# For a deploy, inject it from the bridge `secrets` peer:
#   name=demo_public_missing_write   scope=demo-app
# Never commit a real value (.env* is gitignored; this file is not).
VITE_SONENTA_TOKEN=

# Sonenta API base. Leave UNSET to get the default: https://api.sonenta.com
# (api.sonenta.dev and api.verbumia.dev are the SAME production API — one nginx
# server block, one app, one DB — but a .dev host READS like a staging box to a
# prospect who opens devtools on a public showcase, so prod uses .com.)
# Set to http://localhost:8820 to run the live feedback loop against a local
# backend. See kb topic sdk/demo-live-provisioning.
VITE_SONENTA_API_BASE=

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Realtime — DEV ONLY. It is deliberately NOT in the production build.
#
# Realtime is free developer tooling by locked decision: on a PUBLISHED version
# (prod's `main`) the channel is null and the client never subscribes, so it can
# do nothing in production. And it did not stand down quietly — it gated its
# socket behind an authed /versions/ probe that 401s on this public showcase and
# then FAILED SOFT (warn, carry on), so every visitor paid a failed authed
# request for a subsystem that could never function. `realtimeMode` is derived
# from these vars at build time, so leaving them unset makes the plugin
# statically dead and it drops out of the bundle entirely.
#
# Set the first two to run a dev-version showcase with live updates:
VITE_SONENTA_VERSION=
# `prod` (default, CDN ~60s freshness) or `dev` (live fetch + realtime-eligible).
VITE_SONENTA_ENV=
# Centrifugo node the realtime plugin dials on dev versions (the
# "<host>/connection/websocket" path is fixed). Defaults to
# wss://rt.sonenta.dev/connection/websocket; for a local backend use
# ws://localhost:8830/connection/websocket
VITE_SONENTA_RT_WS=
